      "settings": {
        "bridge_text": "<p>While most brands I've researched source their moringa from third parties and focus only on nutrition or only on skincare, I came across a small Indonesian brand that takes a different approach entirely. Treelogy grows its own moringa on their organic-certified farm in Bali and processes it in their own BPOM-registered facility. From soil to product — everything under one roof.</p><p>That matters more than most people realize. Some of the nutrients in moringa are so fragile that if you can't see how it's made, it's probably being made in a way that destroys them. Treelogy publishes their process openly — which, after weeks of researching this market, I can tell you is rare.</p><p>And the best part? They offer a Starter Pack that lets you try the capsules and powder in smaller sizes — so you can find which format fits your daily routine — along with the seed oil for skin and hair. It's their full inside-and-outside protocol in one box. They're running it at a lower price this month with free shipping while stock lasts.</p>",
