    "quality-proof": {
      "type": "advertorial-quality-proof",
      "settings": {
        "intro_text": "<p>If you're still reading, you probably want to understand exactly why quality matters so much with moringa — and how to tell the difference between the real thing and the cheap alternatives that give the plant a bad name.</p>",
        "inside_outside_image": "shopify://shop_images/make-more-premium.png",
        "subhead": "How to tell real moringa from the brown powder that doesn't work.",
        "body_quality": "<p>Walk into any health store and you'll find moringa powder for Rp 50,000. It's brown. It's bitter. Most of it is ground-up stems.</p><p>Most brands shred the entire branch — leaves, stems, bark — because it's faster and cheaper. The result is a powder that's oxidized before it reaches you. Low absorption. Low potency. That's why so many women try moringa once and give up.</p>",
        "color_comparison_image": "shopify://shop_images/most-brands-shred-the-entire-branch-leaves-stems-bark-because-its-faster-and-cheaper-the-result-is-a-powder-thats-oxidized-before-it-reaches-you-low-absorption-low-potency-thats-why-s.png",
        "body_process": "<p>Leaf-only moringa looks different. Vibrant green, like matcha. The difference comes down to whether the stems were removed — by hand, one leaf at a time.</p><p>This process takes one full hour to produce just 12 grams of powder. Treelogy follows this method for every batch. Harvested at dawn in Karangasem, Bali. Hand-separated. Dehydrated at 38°C for 22 hours to protect heat-sensitive vitamins and enzymes. No shortcuts.</p>",
        "process_image": "shopify://shop_images/leaf-only-moringa-looks-different-vibrant-green-like-matcha-the-difference-comes-down-to-whether-the-stems-were-removed-by-hand-one-leaf-at-a-time-this-process-takes-one-full-hour-to.png"
